🧠 Introduction

GUI (Graphical User Interface) allows users to interact with applications using:

✔ Buttons
✔ Text Boxes
✔ Labels
✔ Menus
✔ Windows

Instead of typing commands in the terminal.

Python provides **Tkinter**, a built-in library for creating desktop applications.

---

🔹 What is Tkinter?

```text id="tkinter_def"
Tkinter is Python's standard GUI library used for creating desktop applications.
```

---

🎯 Why Use Tkinter?

✔ Built into Python
✔ Easy to learn
✔ Cross-platform
✔ Lightweight
✔ Great for beginner GUI projects

